==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tartarous
<hw>Tar"tar*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>tartareux</ets>.]</ety> <def>Containing tartar; consisting of
tartar, or partaking of its qualities; tartareous.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tartarous</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Tartarous
<hw>Tar"tar*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Resembling, or
characteristic of, a Tartar; ill-natured; irritable.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>Tartarous</qex> moods of common men.</q> <rj><qau>B.
Jonson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tartarum</ent>⟦br⟧
